oyment Relations | Industrial Relations | MHRINZ | ESG & Policy Frameworks | DEI | People & Culture Change Management | HR Project Management | Senior Leadership", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/marinussnetler/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAACsdFoBlceYdk_SksgtYwzyfBNxk13IWfo", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "chas worked with Matthew but they were at different companies", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "April 23, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "Matthew worked with the local Scarborough Beach Association to connect the Rendezvous Hotel Group with the local community. Matthew was efficient, open & friendly & we are sad to have lost his expertise back to the east coast.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "chas paridis", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Licencee at Peard & Associates North Beach", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/chas-paridis-68774418/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAOrNscBx01gIF2GwmdJC8Pj0gMs4IDDrzk", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "D. Sean was senior to Matthew but didn't manage Matthew directly", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "February 28, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Matthew was the GM of the Rendezvous Hotel in Brisbane when I assumed responsibility for the Group Operations.  I immediately recognised Matthew as  an excellent GM and a highly effective overall operator in the business.  He greatly assisted me in troubleshooting on the opening of a challenging project, and proved himself to be a great team player.\n\nWhen restructuring the management of our properties in Western Australia, Matthew was my first choice to lead that Region.  His impact was felt immediately with vast improvements to the service, cleanliness, and profitability of the properties under his control.  The performance of his properties has continued to impress and delight all of us at the corporate office.\n\nMatthew is a Star!  I hope that I have the opportunity to work with Matthew again in the future.", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "D. Sean Flynn", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Principal Consultant @ D.S. Flynn & Associates Inc. | Certified Franchise Executive | Lean Six Sigma Black Belt | Author", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dseanflynn/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADHc_0Bex6fNWEgpDwe3YxBLkfaB4y3xxU", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Pat managed Matthew directly", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "August 5, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Matt. His responsibility in the Area General Manager role covers two very busy hotels in Brisbane both of which needed strong leadership and direction when he started in the role. Matt threw himself into the job with great enthusiasm and a no-nonsense leadership style that the staff and managers immediately warmed to. He has performed extremely well in this role and guided the two hotels to high levels of excellence and profitability. I strongly recommend Matt.", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Pat Sheehan CMgr CFIML CAHRI", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "High-Performance Organisational Culture Development | Optimising Leadership, Engagement, Innovation and Performance | Managing Director @ NSC Group | Chartered Fellow", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/patricksheehan/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALAvT0B0rZ8n1czUQvuWZFLgdZxK5ZK7zQ", "skills/0/title": "Revenue Assurance", "skills/1/title": "Direct Sales", "skills/2/title": "Project Management", "skills/3/title": "Business Development", "skills/4/title": "Construction Management", "skills/5/title": "P&L Forecasting", "skills/6/title": "Revenue Generation", "skills/7/title": "Revenue & Profit Growth", "skills/8/title": "Financial Forecasting", "skills/9/title": "Business